# Optional persistent data partition shared across retained versions.
#
# Mount lazily via systemd's automount support so a missing or absent
# DATA partition produces no [TIME]/[DEPEND]/[FAILED] red lines on the
# console at boot. With `noauto,x-systemd.automount` the device is
# only resolved when something actually accesses /mnt/data, and
# `nofail` keeps the failure quiet if the partition genuinely never
# appears (e.g. someone built a disk with --data-size none).
PARTLABEL=DATA /mnt/data ext4 noauto,nofail,x-systemd.automount,x-systemd.device-timeout=2s 0 2
